[58.177422, "o", "# Product Vision вЂ” hello-helix\r\n\r\n## Mission\r\n\r\nProvide a simple, reliable command-line tool for temperature conversion that\r\ndevelopers can drop into scripts, pipelines, and terminal workflows without\r\nreaching for a browser or writing one-off arithmetic.\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n\r\n"]
[58.177535, "o", "Converting between Celsius and Fahrenheit is a common need in scripts, DevOps\r\ntooling, IoT data pipelines, and everyday terminal work. Existing solutions\r\nrequire context-switching to a browser, a calculator, or a custom script that\r\ngets rewritten project after project.\r\n\r\n"]
[58.177643, "o", "...\r\n\r\n"]
[60.179166, "o", "в”Ђв”Ђ docs/helix/01-frame/prd.md в”Ђв”Ђ\r\n"]
[60.180255, "o", "# Product Requirements Document вЂ” hello-helix\r\n\r\n## Overview\r\n\r\n`hello-helix` is a Node.js CLI temperature converter. Users invoke it with a\r\nsingle flag and a numeric value; it prints the converted temperature to stdout.\r\n\r\n## CLI Interface\r\n\r\n```\r\nconvert --to-celsius <temp>      Convert Fahrenheit в†’ Celsius\r\nconvert --to-fahrenheit <temp>   Convert Celsius в†’ Fahrenheit\r\n```\r\n\r\n"]
[60.180281, "o", "Output format: one decimal place, no units suffix (e.g., `100.0`).\r\n\r\n## Features by Priority\r\n\r\n### P0 вЂ” Basic Conversion (MVP)\r\n\r\n"]
[60.18046, "o", "...\r\n\r\n"]
[64.199648, "o", "\r\nв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓ\r\n  ACT 4: Design вЂ” How to Build It\r\n"]
