[205.456807, "o", "\r\nв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓ\r\n  ACT 7: Review\r\nв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓ\r\n\r\n"]
[207.458589, "o", "$ ddx agent run --text \"Review all artifacts and code in this project for errors, omissions, and quality...\"\r\n\r\n"]
[284.851061, "o", "## Review: hello-helix\r\n\r\n### Spec Coverage Matrix\r\n\r\n| Acceptance Criterion | Spec Source | Implemented | Tested |\r\n|---|---|---|---|\r\n| `--to-celsius 212` в†’ `100.0` | FEAT-001 S1 | вњ“ | unit only |\r\n| `--to-celsius 32` в†’ `0.0` | FEAT-001 S1 | вњ“ | вњ— |\r\n| `--to-celsius 98.6` в†’ `37.0` | FEAT-001 S1 | вњ“ | approx only |\r\n| `--to-fahrenheit 0` в†’ `32.0` | FEAT-001 S2 | вњ“ | unit only |\r\n| `--to-fahrenheit 100` в†’ `212.0` | FEAT-001 S2 | вњ“ | вњ— |\r\n| `--to-fahrenheit 37` в†’ `98.6` | FEAT-001 S2 | вњ“ | вњ— |\r\n| Invalid input в†’ stderr + exit 1 | FEAT-001 S3 | вњ“ | вњ— |\r\n| Missing arg в†’ stderr + exit 1 | FEAT-001 S3 | вњ“ | вњ— |\r\n| Unknown flags в†’ stderr + exit 1 | PRD P1-3 | вњ— | вњ— |\r\n| Batch mode (multiple values) | PRD P2 | вњ— | вњ— |\r\n| Output = exactly 1 decimal place | FEAT-001 notes | вњ“ | вњ— |\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Implementation Issues\r\n\r\n- **Unknown flag handling missing** (`bin/convert.js:24-29`) вЂ” if both flags are absent (e.g. `convert --foo 212`), the else-branch fires with a generic usage message. That satisfies the error behavior partially, but any flag other than the two known ones silently falls through to the \"missing arg\" path rather than an explicit \"unknown flag\" error as required by PRD P1-3.\r\n- **Batch mode (P2) not implemented** вЂ” `args[toFFlag + 1]` reads only the first value after the flag; remaining values are silently ignored.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Test Issues\r\n\r\n- **Zero CLI-level tests** вЂ” all 3 tests call `toFahrenheit`/`toCelsius` directly; no test exercises the CLI entrypoint, so exit codes, stderr output, and output formatting (`.toFixed(1)`) are all untested.\r\n- **Only 3 of 6 FEAT-001 conversion cases covered** вЂ” missing: `toCelsius(32)`, `toFahrenheit(100)`, `toFahrenheit(37)`.\r\n- **Approximate assertion for 98.6в†’37** вЂ” uses `< 0.01` tolerance rather than asserting formatted output `\"37.0\"`, so the rounding spec isn't actually verified.\r\n- **No test for P1 error paths** вЂ” invalid input, missing arg, unknown flags all unverified.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Docs Issues\r\n\r\n- **TD-001 usage line** says `node bin/convert.js` but `package.json` has a `bin` entry implying `convert` CLI вЂ” minor inconsistency, low impact.\r\n- **No tracker issue for P2** вЂ” batch mode is spec'd in the PRD but there's no corresponding issue in the tracker (`docs/helix/`) to track its deferred status.\r\n- **FEAT-001 has no \"Not implemented / deferred\" marker** for P2 stories вЂ” a reader would expect P2 to be done.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Summary\r\n\r\n"]
[284.851148, "o", "**Critical gaps:** No CLI integration tests (all P1 AC untested), batch mode unimplemented with no deferral marker, unknown-flag handling incomplete.  \r\n**Minor gaps:** 3 unit-test cases missing, formatting not asserted, docs minor inconsistency.\r\n\r\n"]
[289.855025, "o", "\r\nв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓ\r\n  Demo Complete!\r\nв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓ\r\n\r\n"]
